modules.description: This module implements TLS-secured network communication using Miou's Unix file descriptors. It provides functions for reading from and writing to TLS-encrypted connections, managing connection state with operations like `close` and `shutdown`, and establishing client and server TLS sessions over existing file descriptors. Key use cases include secure client-server communication, implementing TLS-encrypted network services, and integrating TLS handshakes with Unix file descriptor-based IO.
